css selectors - https://www.w3schools.com/cssref/css_selectors.asp
-------------





div.class-name //Selects all divs that have class class-name

div, p  //Selects all <div> elements and all <p> elements

div p // selects all p elements within a div element

div > p // selects all p elements where the parent is a div element

div + p // selects all p elements that are placed directly after a div element

----

p:first-child // every <p> element that is the first child of its parent

p:last-child

p::first-letter // every first letter of every p element

p::first-line // selects the first line of every p element

p:first-of-type // selects every p elements which is the first within its parent

p:last-of-type 

//work around to select first div with .myclass1
//(first div is red all following are yellow)
.myclass1 { color: red; }
.myclass1 ~ .myclass1 { color: yellow; }

input:enabled // selects every enabled input element

----

a:link - a normal, unvisited link
a:visited - a link the user has visited
a:hover - a link when the user mouses over it
a:active - a link the moment it is clicked



